      "comment": "COOL NIGHT (7) should find this easier than his latest attempt at Menangle when sixth after racing outside the leader. Had been racing well prior including a win at this circuit and distance at the previous appearance. Must overcome a wide draw but is up to winning this with even luck. VAN BASTEN (3) did a good job here last week, coming from the back row to be beaten less 3 metres into third. A good draw gives him the chance to return to the winners' list. LOU WILL NZ (6) continues to race well, finishing top-four in his three outings since cruising home by 18m at this venue. Respect. ULTIMATE CRUZA (4) has been racing at Menangle of late so is suited returning to a circuit and distance where he has won five of nine attempts.",
